<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Antennae dark brown, about as long as 
<number box="[659,669,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[680,696,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
of forewing costa, club yellow ventrally; palpi second segment erect, densely covered with long greyish white scales ventrally, third segment long and slender, distinctly protruding.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Wings upperside with ground color brown, unmarked, cilia pale yellow, without secondary sexual characters. Underside of forewing with ground color the same as that on upperside, scattered with yellow scales at apex and the end of cell. Underside hindwing yellow, costa and termen brown, veins yellow, with brown spots in spaces Cu 
<number box="[299,307,408,422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
to Sc+R 
<number box="[406,414,408,422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
and the end of the cell, the area belowr vein Cu 
<number box="[976,984,408,422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
light yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[387,524,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1304,1328]" captionTargetBox="[266,1329,778,1277]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[238,1349,760,1278]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 14. Male genitalia of Idmon bicolora sp. nov. 10. ring, lateral view, 11. tegumen, dorsal view, 12. valva, inner view, 13. aedeagus, 14. juxta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273825/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Figs. 
<number box="[455,524,434,460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10-14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus long, about twice longer than tegumen, deeply and broadly bifid at half distal portion, two arms long and slim, running slightly outwardly; socius absentt; gnathos well developed, membranous and separated each ether at tip; saccus rather long; valva simple, broad, with the distal portion shallow bifid, forming the ampullar and the harpal processes, the ampulla with upper margin hardly swelled, the harpe with lower margin slightly convex, outer margin straight; two processes separated at apex; aedeagus with subzonal sheath subequal to suprazonal sheath, and bifid in distal portion; juxta U-shaped.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273825/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" targetBox="[266,1329,778,1277]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1304,1362]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,1304,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">FIGURES 10–14.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[548,715,1305,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolora" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[548,715,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Idmon bicolora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[722,806,1304,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
10. ring, lateral view, 11. tegumen, dorsal view, 12. valva, inner view, 13. aedeagus, 14. juxta.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1454,1643]" box="[151,244,1454,1480]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Remark</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1454,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Chou &amp; Huang, 1994" authorityName="Chou &amp; Huang" authorityYear="1994" box="[524,1002,1494,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujianana">
<emphasis box="[524,719,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Idmon fujianana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chou" box="[734,993,1494,1520]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" refString="Chou, I. (ed.) (1994) Monographia Rhopalocerorum Sinensium. Henan Scientific and Technological Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 854 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Chou &amp; Huang, 
<number box="[930,993,1494,1520]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily separated from the latter by hindwing underside covered with yellow scales except for costa and termen brown; discocellular margined brown with broad yellow outwardly; the area blow vein Cu 
<number box="[982,990,1590,1604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
pale yellow; valva with the ampallar and harpal processes widely separated at apex.
</paragraph>
